1
00:01:39,116 --> 00:01:41,573
[Episode 18]

2
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,520
Slow down, Cousin.

3
00:01:54,919 --> 00:01:56,560
I-It's so big here.

4
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,594
Excuse me.

5
00:01:57,594 --> 00:02:00,880
So many people, and everyone's all covered up.
How are we supposed to find him?

6
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:02,000
I asked around.

7
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:05,600
This is the Shi family's seafood farm.

8
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,839
You sure Hu is here?

9
00:02:11,839 --> 00:02:14,159
Shi Min said so. The location points here too.

10
00:02:14,159 --> 00:02:15,240
Guess we search.

11
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,280
Let's split up.

12
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:18,458
Sir, have you seen a young guy?

13
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:20,640
Big ears, and he stammers.

14
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:23,279
Is there a new young man working here?

15
00:02:23,279 --> 00:02:25,829
Excuse me. Have you seen a boy about my height?

16
00:02:25,829 --> 00:02:27,240
He stutters a little.

17
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:29,240
Hu!

18
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:30,520
Fan Tong!

19
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,520
Lower your voice. You're bothering people.

20
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:33,559
I want to find him.

21
00:02:33,559 --> 00:02:36,080
Hu!

22
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:38,640
- Qing Ye?
- Fan...

23
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:39,800
Wu.

24
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,520
- Hu?
- Hu.

25
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,559
Fan Tong.

26
00:02:43,559 --> 00:02:45,920
Oh, my poor guy.

27
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:48,560
One day away and you already look like this?

28
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:50,800
What are you wearing?

29
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:53,883
It's nothing. J-Just doing some physical work.

30
00:02:53,883 --> 00:02:57,679
You're here for Shi Min, right?

31
00:02:57,679 --> 00:03:00,360
We called her before we came.

32
00:03:01,422 --> 00:03:02,880
Cousin guessed it long ago.

33
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:04,720
If not for that,
why would we come straight here

34
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:06,600
when there are so many farms on Changdao?

35
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:10,159
Tell us.

36
00:03:10,159 --> 00:03:12,120
What's the whole story?

37
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:17,520
<i>I'm not going to school next week.</i>

38
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:20,440
<i>My dad wants me to drop out.</i>

39
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,879
<i>Don't worry.</i>

40
00:03:21,879 --> 00:03:24,440
<i>W-We'll find a way.</i>

41
00:03:25,399 --> 00:03:26,706
<i>Hu.</i>

42
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:27,760
<i>Hu.</i>

43
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:30,468
<i>- Where'd this kid go?
- Mom.</i>

44
00:03:30,468 --> 00:03:31,879
<i>Why are you hiding there?</i>

45
00:03:31,879 --> 00:03:34,159
<i>Did you do your homework?</i>

46
00:03:34,159 --> 00:03:35,599
<i>I'll go do it right now.</i>

47
00:03:35,599 --> 00:03:37,299
<i>Hurry up. Take this medicine.</i>

48
00:03:37,299 --> 00:03:38,360
<i>It's for your stutter.</i>

49
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,960
<i>W-What's this? It's all dark and gross.</i>

50
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:42,768
<i>Miracle medicine.</i>

51
00:03:42,768 --> 00:03:44,843
<i>A-Another folk remedy?</i>

52
00:03:44,843 --> 00:03:46,200
<i>No, it's not.</i>

53
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:49,399
<i>Your aunt sent it all the way from Tianjin.</i>

54
00:03:49,399 --> 00:03:51,279
<i>She said the doctor is really good.</i>

55
00:03:51,279 --> 00:03:52,999
<i>A few doses and it'll work.</i>

56
00:03:52,999 --> 00:03:54,480
<i>Come on, drink it up.</i>

57
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:56,320
<i>Y-Y-You go do your thing.</i>

58
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:57,480
<i>I'll drink it in a bit.</i>

59
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:59,679
<i>Drink it now. It won't work if it's cold.</i>

60
00:03:59,679 --> 00:04:01,220
<i>Don't you pour it out. Drink it.</i>

61
00:04:01,220 --> 00:04:02,794
<i>I'm watching you.</i>

62
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:08,960
<i>I heard from Mr. Zhu
that your grades are stuck.</i>

63
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:11,259
<i>What's going on?</i>

64
00:04:11,999 --> 00:04:13,640
<i>I don't...</i>

65
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,599
<i>Listen to me, Fan Tong.</i>

66
00:04:15,599 --> 00:04:17,479
<i>I'm not trying to pressure you.</i>

67
00:04:17,479 --> 00:04:20,372
<i>But the Gaokao is next year.</i>

68
00:04:20,372 --> 00:04:22,200
<i>If you can't get your grades up,</i>

69
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:25,520
<i>you won't make it to college,
and you won't find a job.</i>

70
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:27,240
<i>Without a job, you won't get a good wife.</i>

71
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:29,400
<i>What will you do then?
You can't end up like your dad,</i>

72
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:31,280
<i>stuck here your whole life. You get me?</i>

73
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:33,039
<i>I'm going to do my homework.</i>

74
00:04:33,039 --> 00:04:34,560
<i>What should I do?</i>

75
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:36,882
<i>My dad just doesn't agree.</i>

76
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:39,720
<i>Who is that girl?</i>

77
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:40,919
<i>What does she mean?</i>

78
00:04:40,919 --> 00:04:42,359
<i>- Y-You heard wrong.
- Who disagrees?</i>

79
00:04:42,359 --> 00:04:44,399
<i>- No, nothing. Mom, you…
- Nothing?</i>

80
00:04:44,399 --> 00:04:45,640
<i>You heard it wrong.</i>

81
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,680
<i>- Are you in an online relationship?
- I...</i>

82
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:48,848
<i>No wonder you're not studying hard.</i>

83
00:04:48,848 --> 00:04:50,479
<i>- That's why your grades are bad.
- It's not…</i>

84
00:04:50,479 --> 00:04:53,200
<i>Look at you. You can't even finish a sentence.
What girl would ever like you?</i>

85
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:56,080
<i>If you don't study hard, you'll be done for.</i>

86
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,280
I get it now.

87
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:01,479
Shi Min's dad is making her drop out.
You tried to talk her out of it.

88
00:05:01,479 --> 00:05:02,680
But your mom

89
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:05,480
thought it was an online relationship.

90
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,640
So with all that pressure,

91
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:09,720
you ran away from home

92
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,612
and came here to Shi Min?

93
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:15,640
I-I'm not trying to anger my mom.

94
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:18,720
I-I just came to talk to Shi Min's dad

95
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:20,599
and ask him not to make her drop out.

96
00:05:20,599 --> 00:05:22,640
She couldn't even persuade her dad herself.

97
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:24,000
What makes you think you can?

98
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,239
B-But Qing Ye managed to convince Xing Wu.

99
00:05:26,239 --> 00:05:30,000
W-Why can't I succeed?

100
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,720
So did you?

101
00:05:40,039 --> 00:05:41,680
Almost.

102
00:06:04,479 --> 00:06:06,840
<i>Which one of you is Shi Jian Guo?</i>

103
00:06:13,839 --> 00:06:15,919
<i>G-Get him out here.</i>

104
00:06:15,919 --> 00:06:18,040
<i>I've got something to say to him.</i>

105
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:22,310
<i>Hey Sir,</i>

106
00:06:22,310 --> 00:06:24,360
<i>where's Shi Jia Guo?</i>

107
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:28,760
<i>Who's looking for me?</i>

108
00:06:33,493 --> 00:06:34,520
<i>Who are you?</i>

109
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:36,000
<i>What do you want?</i>

110
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,585
<i>I...</i>

111
00:06:38,479 --> 00:06:40,799
<i>I-I...</i>

112
00:06:40,799 --> 00:06:44,346
<i>- I heard...
- You heard we're short on help, right?</i>

113
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,520
<i>You're a bit skinny.</i>

114
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:50,000
<i>Whatever, you're hired.</i>

115
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,799
<i>20 yuan an hour. Daily pay.</i>

116
00:06:52,799 --> 00:06:55,200
<i>Take all of these.</i>

117
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,760
<i>Hurry up.</i>

118
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,400
<i>Now get to work.</i>

119
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:08,120
Come on, you call that "almost"?

120
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:10,520
You haven't even started.

121
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:12,239
Don't get down.
At least you got to talk to him.

122
00:07:12,239 --> 00:07:15,920
Yeah, right. Plus you got paid
for half a day's work.

123
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:18,919
Look, Qing Ye, you're so smart.

124
00:07:18,919 --> 00:07:20,520
Just help Shi Min out.

125
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:22,479
You there, the new guy.

126
00:07:22,479 --> 00:07:23,599
Are you done with your work?

127
00:07:23,599 --> 00:07:25,677
That's Shi Min's dad.

128
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:31,080
Who are you guys?

129
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:32,920
Hello, uncle. I'm Shi Min's deskmate.

130
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,399
My name is Qing Ye.

131
00:07:34,399 --> 00:07:36,359
Yes. We're all Shi Min's classmates.

132
00:07:36,359 --> 00:07:37,919
We want to talk to you.

133
00:07:37,919 --> 00:07:39,599
Talk to me?

134
00:07:39,599 --> 00:07:41,080
About what?

135
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:44,228
If it's about school, don't even bother.

136
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:47,760
No, uncle.

137
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,279
We actually want to help out.

138
00:07:49,279 --> 00:07:52,080
The oyster harvest is good.
We heard you're short on hands.

139
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:53,240
We're from Zhazhating.

140
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,359
We've got experience with seaside work.

141
00:07:55,359 --> 00:07:56,400
We're at your service.

142
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:58,320
Min Min never mentioned it.

143
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:00,560
I always thought
she didn't have any friends at school.

144
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:02,039
You probably don't know.

145
00:08:02,039 --> 00:08:03,120
She's really easygoing.

146
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:05,479
- We all get along with her.
- Right.

147
00:08:05,479 --> 00:08:08,200
- Looks like my girl's all grown up.
- Dad.

148
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,280
You're here.

149
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,960
- They told me they're your classmates.
- Yes.

150
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:13,520
And they said they're here to help us.

151
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:14,880
Yeah.

152
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,359
We're here to help.

153
00:08:17,359 --> 00:08:19,640
Alright. Come with me.

154
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:21,160
You too.

155
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,200
What's going on?

156
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,560
Follow him. He's going to give us work.

157
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:27,680
Let's go help first.

158
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,400
Play it by ear.

159
00:08:30,599 --> 00:08:32,280
We should let Mr. Zhu know.

160
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:34,400
I already texted him.

161
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,359
- Move it, quick.
- Okay, okay.

162
00:08:50,359 --> 00:08:51,999
Slow down.

163
00:08:51,999 --> 00:08:54,160
- Slow down.
- Okay, okay.

164
00:08:55,239 --> 00:08:56,920
- How much longer?
- 15 minutes.

165
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,359
Mr. Zhu?

166
00:08:59,359 --> 00:09:00,720
- Mr. Zhu.
- Why are you here?

167
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,160
What are you doing here?

168
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:04,200
What a coincidence. You guys are also…

169
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,920
- Going to Changdao?
- Hurry, hurry.

170
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,880
Quick, quick. Hurry up.

171
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:30,479
Come on, tell me.

172
00:09:30,479 --> 00:09:32,440
What do you like about her?

173
00:09:34,719 --> 00:09:36,719
D-Don't talk nonsense.

174
00:09:36,719 --> 00:09:38,680
What's the big deal?

175
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:41,840
I like my cousin
and I never keep it to myself.

176
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:44,200
Shi Min and I are just good friends.

177
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:46,086
Good friends?

178
00:09:46,086 --> 00:09:47,920
What kind of good friends?

179
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,080
Like,

180
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:51,410
whatever I say, she gets it.

181
00:09:51,410 --> 00:09:53,920
And whatever she says, I get it too.

182
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:55,640
Soulmates.

183
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,680
I guess so.

184
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,800
We're kind of in the same boat.

185
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,759
We both know no matter how hard we try,

186
00:10:02,759 --> 00:10:04,800
it won't matter.

187
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,080
I want to help her.

188
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:09,160
It's like helping myself.

189
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:11,120
So what are you going to do?

190
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:14,280
She's into painting.

191
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:16,479
But her dad won't let her. So…

192
00:10:16,479 --> 00:10:17,560
Painting?

193
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:18,920
How can you help with that?

194
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:20,359
Your family runs a restaurant.

195
00:10:20,359 --> 00:10:22,040
It's not like you can paint for her.

196
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:24,839
And let's be honest,
you couldn't even talk her dad into it.

197
00:10:24,839 --> 00:10:27,840
Well, I never thought I'd end up working here.

198
00:10:28,639 --> 00:10:30,719
Have some more oysters.

199
00:10:30,719 --> 00:10:34,560
Bulk up a bit. I bet you get all shaky
when you talk to her dad, don't you?

200
00:10:36,119 --> 00:10:37,560
Forget it.

201
00:10:38,479 --> 00:10:40,320
You wouldn't understand.

202
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:44,479
Why not?

203
00:10:44,479 --> 00:10:46,840
Take my cousin for example.

204
00:10:47,479 --> 00:10:49,360
I like her.

205
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,639
But I know I'll never be good enough for her

206
00:10:50,639 --> 00:10:52,560
no matter how hard I try.

207
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,479
People like us are lucky

208
00:10:55,479 --> 00:10:57,680
if we can even look after ourselves.

209
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,800
You can't force the shell open.

210
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,154
Use technique.

211
00:11:11,154 --> 00:11:12,760
Push down

212
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:13,999
with your wrist and thumb,

213
00:11:13,999 --> 00:11:16,000
and the knife will pop it open.

214
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:19,320
It's open.

215
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:22,280
Shi Min, is this what you do

216
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,560
when you're not studying?

217
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:24,599
Yes.

218
00:11:24,599 --> 00:11:26,479
We used to only harvest oysters in winter.

219
00:11:26,479 --> 00:11:28,320
But with better fish farming,

220
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,639
we do a summer harvest now too.

221
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:31,639
My family's been doing this for over ten years.

222
00:11:31,639 --> 00:11:34,000
We live off the sea, you know.

223
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,479
So…

224
00:11:35,479 --> 00:11:37,400
so you have to do this much every day?

225
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:40,320
With quick hands,
we can get through 20 jin a day.

226
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:42,560
About twice what you see here.

227
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:45,320
What's the point of shucking them?

228
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:47,080
Can't you sell them as is?

229
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,999
Selling them whole is only four yuan per jin.

230
00:11:48,999 --> 00:11:51,840
The shucked meat goes for 20.

231
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:55,320
Four yuan a jin?

232
00:11:56,519 --> 00:11:59,160
One oyster costs 20 in Beijing.

233
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:00,519
That much?

234
00:12:00,519 --> 00:12:02,752
At a fancy restaurant,

235
00:12:02,752 --> 00:12:04,480
it'd be even more.

236
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:08,360
Those must be really nice restaurants, I guess.

237
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:12,320
I knew our catch goes for higher prices
away from here.

238
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,760
But I didn't expect it to jump that high.

239
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:18,239
Shi Min,

240
00:12:18,239 --> 00:12:20,440
have you ever thought about

241
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,760
leaving this place

242
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:23,797
and seeing the outside world?

243
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:27,639
It's not in the cards for me.

244
00:12:27,639 --> 00:12:28,800
My dad said

245
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,560
studying is useless.

246
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:31,920
And anyway,

247
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:34,210
I try so hard

248
00:12:34,210 --> 00:12:36,434
but I still rank last in exams.

249
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,160
Maybe I should just listen to my dad

250
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:41,560
and stay on Changdao my whole life.

251
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:43,040
Grow oysters.

252
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:44,759
Harvest oysters.

253
00:12:44,759 --> 00:12:46,640
Shuck oysters.

254
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,520
But what about you?

255
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:52,640
What do you think yourself?

256
00:12:55,599 --> 00:12:57,280
Me?

257
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:04,080
I don't want to shuck oysters anymore.

258
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:06,040
And I'm done with drying nets

259
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:07,920
and gutting fish.

260
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,280
So tell me,

261
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:14,080
what is it you really want to do?

262
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:15,920
I want to paint.

263
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:19,160
But it's just a dream.

264
00:13:46,759 --> 00:13:48,119
Uncle,

265
00:13:48,119 --> 00:13:50,359
this farm of yours is really big.

266
00:13:50,359 --> 00:13:51,960
You must make decent money, right?

267
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:54,720
Are you short on help?

268
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:58,639
It pays okay.

269
00:13:58,639 --> 00:14:01,759
But when harvest season comes,
we're really short-handed.

270
00:14:01,759 --> 00:14:05,479
Changdao has many elderly people
but few middle-aged ones.

271
00:14:05,479 --> 00:14:07,560
As for the young,
none of them like doing this work.

272
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:10,560
And this year, Min Min's sister had a baby.

273
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:12,560
Her mom went to help with the postpartum care.

274
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:15,280
That's why I had Min Min come home to help me.

275
00:14:17,999 --> 00:14:19,759
Looks like

276
00:14:19,759 --> 00:14:21,879
Shi Min has won quite a few certificates.

277
00:14:21,879 --> 00:14:24,517
That shows she's doing really well at school.

278
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,661
Sure, Min Min studied well

279
00:14:27,661 --> 00:14:29,040
as a kid.

280
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:32,119
But after starting high school,
she couldn't keep up at all.

281
00:14:32,119 --> 00:14:34,879
But the teachers all say she works really hard.

282
00:14:34,879 --> 00:14:36,120
Maybe she just hasn't found

283
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:38,080
the right method yet.

284
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:40,999
You're just a kid. You don't get it.

285
00:14:40,999 --> 00:14:42,200
You know what?

286
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:44,202
If you're working toward the wrong goal,

287
00:14:44,202 --> 00:14:46,680
the harder you try, the more you go off track.

288
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:48,440
Look at this big farm.

289
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,160
Someone's got to take it over one day.

290
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,920
And that'll be Min Min, no doubt.

291
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:55,000
After she starts earning,
she can do whatever she wants.

292
00:14:57,519 --> 00:15:00,851
I still don't know what I can do in the future.

293
00:15:00,851 --> 00:15:02,438
But I do know

294
00:15:02,438 --> 00:15:05,200
this life right now isn't the one I want.

295
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:08,320
I want to spend every day drawing,

296
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:11,160
not every day stuck here.

297
00:15:11,879 --> 00:15:13,960
Qing Ye,

298
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:16,760
I really want to go out there
and see the world.

299
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:39,839
<i>You painted this?</i>

300
00:15:39,839 --> 00:15:41,360
<i>It's really good.</i>

301
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:43,625
<i>It's... just a doodle.</i>

302
00:15:49,599 --> 00:15:51,400
I support you.

303
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:53,560
Look,

304
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:55,999
your family business is huge.

305
00:15:55,999 --> 00:15:57,240
I mean,

306
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:59,560
money won't be a struggle for you.

307
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:02,400
Maybe you should give it a try.

308
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,080
Talk to your dad

309
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,120
and get him

310
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:07,105
to let you study art.

311
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:11,320
But my dad says being an artist is unrealistic.

312
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:13,800
Better to run this business with
all the fish and shrimp and oysters.

313
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:15,839
That's not how it is.

314
00:16:15,839 --> 00:16:18,479
Studying art opens up so many jobs.

315
00:16:18,479 --> 00:16:20,400
You could do architectural design,

316
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:22,280
fashion design,

317
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:23,600
or be a teacher.

318
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:26,239
You could be an art teacher.

319
00:16:26,239 --> 00:16:27,519
You're right.

320
00:16:27,519 --> 00:16:28,760
Qing Ye,

321
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:31,804
will you help me talk my dad around?

322
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:36,440
I promise. I'll definitely help you.

323
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:38,160
Thank you.

324
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:47,719
Put a little of this on.

325
00:16:47,719 --> 00:16:49,639
- What's this?
- Clam oil.

326
00:16:49,639 --> 00:16:51,160
All-natural formula.

327
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:52,719
It nourishes skin and prevents cracking.

328
00:16:52,719 --> 00:16:55,350
Sort of a seaside specialty, I suppose.

329
00:17:00,719 --> 00:17:02,119
The smell is kind of strange.

330
00:17:02,119 --> 00:17:04,105
But it really works.

331
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:11,840
That's not enough.

332
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:13,759
Need to put it on thick.

333
00:17:13,759 --> 00:17:15,320
Here.

334
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:19,280
That's how it works.

335
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:24,077
Don't leave out any spots.

336
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,000
Done.

337
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:43,080
It's yours now.

338
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:53,240
Xing Wu,

339
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:55,495
can I see your hand?

340
00:17:56,079 --> 00:17:57,520
What for?

341
00:18:17,479 --> 00:18:19,200
Shi Min said

342
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,840
everyone around here

343
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:23,042
gets these calluses on their hands.

344
00:18:24,559 --> 00:18:26,479
It's a coastal thing.

345
00:18:26,479 --> 00:18:28,360
Harvesting oysters is tough work.

346
00:18:28,360 --> 00:18:30,200
Many women do this job for decades.

347
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,264
When they're old,

348
00:18:31,264 --> 00:18:33,252
they can't even straighten their fingers.

349
00:18:34,799 --> 00:18:37,400
Everyone says coastal folks are tough as nails.

350
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,079
The truth is, you guys have it really hard.

351
00:18:39,079 --> 00:18:41,000
So I want to try my best

352
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,556
to help Shi Min.

353
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:45,760
Zhu should give you

354
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:48,297
a "Best Sidekick for School Returns" award.

355
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:50,360
People only come back

356
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,849
because they want to.

357
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:55,868
Same goes for you.

358
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:58,560
Doesn't it?

359
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:02,460
I'm not really the same

360
00:19:02,460 --> 00:19:04,019
as Shi Min.

361
00:19:32,479 --> 00:19:33,979
Hu!

362
00:19:33,979 --> 00:19:35,885
Hu!

363
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:39,160
Hu!

364
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,640
Hu!

365
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:42,680
Hu!

366
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,319
Be careful.

367
00:19:45,319 --> 00:19:47,261
Hu!

368
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:49,840
You scared me to death.

369
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:51,759
Auntie.

370
00:19:51,759 --> 00:19:53,200
Oh my god.

371
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,840
- You okay?
- All good, all good.

372
00:19:54,840 --> 00:19:56,239
Auntie.

373
00:19:56,239 --> 00:19:57,799
Fuzz.

374
00:19:57,799 --> 00:20:00,160
Why didn't you two tell me before you left?

375
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:02,200
Look how worried they are.

376
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:04,239
- We were in a rush.
- Yeah.

377
00:20:04,239 --> 00:20:06,840
- Where's Fuzz? Is he here?
- We're all here.

378
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:08,512
Fuzz!

379
00:20:08,512 --> 00:20:09,719
Fuzz!

380
00:20:09,719 --> 00:20:11,719
I was wrong yesterday.

381
00:20:11,719 --> 00:20:13,559
I shouldn't have scolded you.

382
00:20:13,559 --> 00:20:15,279
Do whatever you want from now on.

383
00:20:15,279 --> 00:20:17,160
If you're okay with your stutter,
then skip the medicine.

384
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:20,400
Just don't run away from home
and don't scare me again. Okay?

385
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:22,400
I didn't run away.

386
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:25,200
I just... I just came to help a classmate.

387
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,279
Okay, I believe you.

388
00:20:26,279 --> 00:20:28,160
Whatever you say from now on,
I'll believe you.

389
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:30,479
It was my fault. I'm sorry.

390
00:20:30,479 --> 00:20:32,559
Don't be like this. Go sit over there.

391
00:20:32,559 --> 00:20:35,240
Where did Fuzz go?

392
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:43,719
So here you are. You brat!
How dare you hide from me?

393
00:20:43,719 --> 00:20:45,680
Mom, Mom, Mom. Let me explain, Mom.

394
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:48,480
What's there to explain?
You took the boat out without even telling me.

395
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:49,560
What if something happened?

396
00:20:49,560 --> 00:20:51,387
Listen to me, Mom. If you hit me again,

397
00:20:51,387 --> 00:20:52,880
I'll run away from home just like Hu.

398
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:55,319
You dare run away? I'll...

399
00:20:55,319 --> 00:20:57,279
Auntie Fang!

400
00:20:57,279 --> 00:20:58,600
- Auntie, auntie, auntie.
- Enough now.

401
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:00,520
Auntie, it was my idea.
We couldn't wait for the ferry.

402
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:01,960
So we just took the boat ourselves.

403
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:04,360
Wu, this isn't on you.

404
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,600
I know you.

405
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,999
You're a good kid.

406
00:21:06,999 --> 00:21:09,239
Today I'm going to teach him a lesson.

407
00:21:09,239 --> 00:21:11,079
Stop right there. I said stop! Stop!

408
00:21:11,079 --> 00:21:12,120
Go easy on him then.

409
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:14,040
Don't worry. I'll beat him to a pulp.

410
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:16,840
Fuzz! Stop!

411
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:18,120
You're really something now.

412
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,640
Your idea, was it?

413
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:21,200
It's no big deal.

414
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,999
Auntie, I learned how to shuck oysters.

415
00:21:23,999 --> 00:21:25,160
So you're a big shot too now.

416
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:27,123
Don't ever do that again.

417
00:21:27,123 --> 00:21:29,239
Oh no. We forgot about him. Quick, quick.

418
00:21:29,239 --> 00:21:30,600
- Mr. Zhu. Mr. Zhu.
- He's seasick.

419
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,519
- I'm fine.
- He got seasick.

420
00:21:32,519 --> 00:21:35,518
On a boat this big,
and he still can't handle it.

421
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,560
Spit it out, and you'll be fine.

422
00:21:40,519 --> 00:21:42,120
Son.

423
00:21:42,960 --> 00:21:44,520
On the way over here,

424
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:45,799
I thought it through.

425
00:21:45,799 --> 00:21:49,400
I shouldn't push my ideas on you.

426
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:52,440
You should have your own life

427
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:55,000
and live the way you want.

428
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:58,160
Son,

429
00:21:58,160 --> 00:22:00,320
I'm really sorry.

430
00:22:01,999 --> 00:22:03,920
Can you forgive me?

431
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:09,440
Mom,

432
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:10,960
don't worry.

433
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:13,319
I'll definitely live for myself.

434
00:22:13,319 --> 00:22:14,960
And for your sake,

435
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:18,179
I'll definitely get into a good college.

436
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,880
Let's go. I'm fine, really.

437
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:25,319
We want to convince her dad
to let her go back to school.

438
00:22:25,319 --> 00:22:26,759
But that's a tough one.

439
00:22:26,759 --> 00:22:27,920
Yeah, right.

440
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:29,282
Totally.

441
00:22:30,039 --> 00:22:31,268
Mr. Zhu, why are you here too?

442
00:22:31,268 --> 00:22:33,239
Here, have some water.

443
00:22:33,239 --> 00:22:34,360
Auntie, you too.

444
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:36,400
Okay, thank you.

445
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:37,840
So this is your classmate?

446
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:39,319
Yes. Shi Min.

447
00:22:39,319 --> 00:22:40,479
The one Hu...

448
00:22:40,479 --> 00:22:41,640
Auntie, water for you.

449
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,200
Thank you.

450
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:45,160
Mom, this is the classmate I told you about.

451
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:46,640
Shi Min.

452
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:50,240
This girl looks pretty well-behaved.

453
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:51,593
You know,

454
00:22:51,593 --> 00:22:55,120
this girl and Hu are kind of...

455
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:56,360
Don't talk nonsense.

456
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:57,920
They're good classmates.

457
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,319
Good friends.

458
00:22:59,319 --> 00:23:01,640
Yeah, yeah, good classmates.

459
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:03,000
Anyway, we're already here,

460
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,632
and there's no rush to go back.

461
00:23:04,632 --> 00:23:06,560
Why don't we help Shi Min with some work?

462
00:23:06,560 --> 00:23:08,640
Please don't, Mr. Zhu. That wouldn't be right.

463
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:10,519
It's okay. We'll help.

464
00:23:10,519 --> 00:23:12,759
We women from Zhazhating can handle this work

465
00:23:12,759 --> 00:23:14,760
even with our eyes closed. Right?

466
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:16,000
And the kids can take a break.

467
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,680
Yeah. You kids rest. We'll take over.

468
00:23:17,680 --> 00:23:21,075
- Don't worry. Let's go.
- Thank you.

469
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:28,519
See? The oysters here are really fresh.

470
00:23:28,519 --> 00:23:30,691
And they're big and plump.

471
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:33,559
Oysters are great.

472
00:23:33,559 --> 00:23:34,957
Yep.

473
00:23:34,957 --> 00:23:36,320
A man's power-up

474
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:37,840
and a woman's spa treatment.

475
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:41,080
You should take some home
to your husband, then.

476
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:47,390
Oh my gosh.

477
00:23:47,390 --> 00:23:48,615
Mr. Zhu,

478
00:23:48,615 --> 00:23:49,880
are you alright?

479
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,720
I'm so sorry.

480
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:53,958
Just leave it here. I'll do it later.

481
00:23:53,958 --> 00:23:56,279
To be honest, Mr. Zhu,

482
00:23:56,279 --> 00:23:58,640
I'm grateful for your kindness.
But just drop it.

483
00:23:58,640 --> 00:23:59,880
No way.

484
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,559
I need to do more.

485
00:24:01,559 --> 00:24:02,840
If not,

486
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:04,400
my students will have to do extra.

487
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:06,087
The thing is,

488
00:24:06,087 --> 00:24:07,600
you're not really helping all that much.

489
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,200
Having you here as a helper

490
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,840
is actually slowing me down.

491
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:13,240
Seriously, Shi,

492
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:14,640
are you really

493
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:16,680
going to let Shi Min drop out?

494
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:21,437
You can't get a refund
for this semester's tuition, you know.

495
00:24:21,437 --> 00:24:22,880
That doesn't matter.

496
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:24,920
I don't care about that bit of money.

497
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:26,680
The point is, there's no way

498
00:24:26,680 --> 00:24:29,079
she's getting into college.

499
00:24:29,079 --> 00:24:30,680
Instead of wasting time on books,

500
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,920
she's better off helping earn money.

501
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,480
Makes sense.

502
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:37,240
Look, you have

503
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:39,920
this huge aquaculture farm.

504
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:43,119
You must be really short on help, right?

505
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:45,092
I'll be honest.

506
00:24:45,092 --> 00:24:46,359
When I was young,

507
00:24:46,359 --> 00:24:47,880
I never felt tired and worked like crazy.

508
00:24:47,880 --> 00:24:50,880
But now I'm older.
Every illness has come knocking.

509
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:54,400
My body fails me more every year.

510
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:56,486
You're not even that old.

511
00:24:56,486 --> 00:24:58,839
I mean, Shi Min is a girl.

512
00:24:58,839 --> 00:25:00,080
Are you really okay

513
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:01,960
with putting her through all this?

514
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,160
Mr. Zhu,

515
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:04,839
I'm her father.

516
00:25:04,839 --> 00:25:06,359
If she were

517
00:25:06,359 --> 00:25:07,519
any good at school,

518
00:25:07,519 --> 00:25:08,640
I'd be happy to send her.

519
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:10,279
But she just doesn't have it in her.

520
00:25:10,279 --> 00:25:12,720
Who told you that?

521
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:14,119
Don't you know?

522
00:25:14,119 --> 00:25:17,599
Shi Min is great at drawing. And she loves it.

523
00:25:17,599 --> 00:25:18,960
Did you ever think about

524
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:21,939
letting her study art and take the art exam?

525
00:25:22,839 --> 00:25:24,744
Study art?

526
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:27,993
My family's been fishermen for generations.

527
00:25:27,993 --> 00:25:30,000
We've never had an artist.

528
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:31,785
Maybe Shi Min is that exception.

529
00:25:32,685 --> 00:25:33,799
You know what?

530
00:25:33,799 --> 00:25:38,160
There's a national policy for art students now.

531
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:41,160
If her art scores are high enough,

532
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,200
lower grades in academics

533
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,360
won't be a big deal.

534
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:45,660
Really? That good?

535
00:25:45,660 --> 00:25:48,880
But if she's still at the bottom of the class,

536
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:51,170
it's just a waste of time.

537
00:25:53,040 --> 00:25:56,519
How could going to school be a waste of time?

538
00:25:56,519 --> 00:25:59,440
That young man who fixed your radio.

539
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:01,799
The tall one, Xing Wu.

540
00:26:01,799 --> 00:26:03,640
He dropped out for two years.

541
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:05,920
And I managed to talk him
into coming back to school.

542
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:08,109
Two years off?

543
00:26:08,873 --> 00:26:10,160
That boy's got

544
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:11,824
some real courage.

545
00:26:13,645 --> 00:26:14,960
Look, I'm a teacher.

546
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,080
The most important thing

547
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:18,599
I should teach them
is the courage to face life.

548
00:26:18,599 --> 00:26:19,720
Shi,

549
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:21,448
I've been a teacher for many years,

550
00:26:21,448 --> 00:26:24,206
and I've taught a lot of students.

551
00:26:24,206 --> 00:26:28,319
Maybe not every one of my students
will become a success.

552
00:26:28,319 --> 00:26:29,800
But

553
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:32,119
I taught them

554
00:26:32,119 --> 00:26:33,600
how to choose the path

555
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:35,440
they truly want.

556
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:39,314
So they can try their best
not to do things they'll regret.

557
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:53,640
I want to toast you all.

558
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:54,840
All of you here

559
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:57,160
are Min Min's classmates and good friends.

560
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:58,319
Plus Mr. Zhu

561
00:26:58,319 --> 00:27:00,440
and three ladies.

562
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:02,455
You guys came all this way to help me out.

563
00:27:02,455 --> 00:27:05,160
I'm really, really grateful.

564
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:07,840
You know, I'm not good with fancy words.

565
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:09,920
I just hope you eat well, drink well,
and have fun.

566
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:10,946
Bottoms up.

567
00:27:10,946 --> 00:27:12,960
- Okay, thank you.
- Yeah, thank you.

568
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:14,566
Come on, cheers.

569
00:27:14,566 --> 00:27:16,000
Cheers.

570
00:27:17,926 --> 00:27:19,492
Mr. Zhu.

571
00:27:19,492 --> 00:27:21,799
- Cheers, Mr. Zhu.
- Dig in.

572
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,920
Thank you.

573
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:26,966
Here, have some shrimp.

574
00:27:26,966 --> 00:27:28,398
It's alright.

575
00:27:28,398 --> 00:27:30,720
Thank you. Appreciate it.

576
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:33,760
It's so hard to find workers these days.

577
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:36,240
No one wants to come even if you pay them.

578
00:27:36,240 --> 00:27:37,906
It's all thanks to you today.

579
00:27:37,906 --> 00:27:39,160
Especially you three ladies.

580
00:27:39,160 --> 00:27:42,480
You did beautiful, fast work.

581
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:44,720
Please, Shi.

582
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:46,640
Don't say that.

583
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:48,216
We're all friends here.

584
00:27:48,216 --> 00:27:49,440
Actually, my husband is the same.

585
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:52,279
When fishing season starts,
he's so busy I can't even find him.

586
00:27:52,279 --> 00:27:54,279
I know that. Things will be fine
after this period's over.

587
00:27:54,279 --> 00:27:56,200
- Yes, that's right.
- We had no idea

588
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:58,039
the kids were this close.

589
00:27:58,039 --> 00:27:59,119
Otherwise,

590
00:27:59,119 --> 00:28:00,400
we'd have come to help much sooner.

591
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:01,720
- Exactly.
- Thank you.

592
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:03,072
Hu's always

593
00:28:03,072 --> 00:28:05,000
been kind-hearted since he was little.

594
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:07,519
I didn't know he came to help a classmate.

595
00:28:07,519 --> 00:28:09,000
I totally misunderstood.

596
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:10,160
Hu's a good boy.

597
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:11,519
- Eat.
- Yes, he is.

598
00:28:11,519 --> 00:28:13,560
Every family has its struggles.

599
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:15,799
But many hands make light work.

600
00:28:15,799 --> 00:28:18,720
Next time you need people, just call us.

601
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,079
Whoever is free will come.

602
00:28:20,079 --> 00:28:22,421
Okay, okay.

603
00:28:23,067 --> 00:28:24,200
I'm sorry for all the trouble

604
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:26,319
Min Min has caused you.

605
00:28:26,319 --> 00:28:28,599
Actually, I know what you mean.

606
00:28:28,599 --> 00:28:32,160
You didn't just come to help me out.
Right, Mr. Zhu?

607
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:35,119
Speaking of which,

608
00:28:35,119 --> 00:28:37,799
Min Min, it's your turn to speak up.

609
00:28:37,799 --> 00:28:40,799
Do you still want to go to school?

610
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:55,160
Shi Jian Guo, I'm going to be clear today.

611
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:59,359
I want to study.

612
00:28:59,359 --> 00:29:00,839
I need to study.

613
00:29:00,839 --> 00:29:03,119
I have to study.

614
00:29:08,799 --> 00:29:10,200
You say my grades are bad.

615
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:12,760
But I work hard every day.

616
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:14,279
You say I can't be an artist.

617
00:29:14,279 --> 00:29:15,519
Maybe that's true. But painting

618
00:29:15,519 --> 00:29:17,359
doesn't mean I have to be an artist.

619
00:29:17,359 --> 00:29:18,600
I could…

620
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:20,318
I could be a teacher.

621
00:29:20,318 --> 00:29:21,840
I could study design.

622
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:25,000
I can do lots of jobs.

623
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:27,018
- Right.
- Right.

624
00:29:27,839 --> 00:29:30,239
- Well said.
- I'm not finished yet.

625
00:29:30,239 --> 00:29:32,105
Go on, kid. Go on.

626
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:34,400
Dad,

627
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:36,559
I want to leave Anzi County.

628
00:29:36,559 --> 00:29:37,880
I want to get into college

629
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:40,920
and study what I really love.

630
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:43,946
I want to go see the outside world.

631
00:29:52,279 --> 00:29:54,160
Right. You're right.

632
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:55,440
- Well said.
- Right.

633
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:57,267
Yeah, right.

634
00:29:59,975 --> 00:30:02,680
But Mr. Zhu told me.

635
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:05,840
If you have to study
both your regular classes and painting,

636
00:30:05,840 --> 00:30:08,000
time will be tight
and the pressure will be even greater.

637
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:11,279
What will you do if your grades
are still at the bottom?

638
00:30:11,279 --> 00:30:13,359
I'll help her, uncle. Don't worry.

639
00:30:13,359 --> 00:30:15,325
I'll study with Shi Min.

640
00:30:15,325 --> 00:30:17,083
There are over 200 days until the Gaokao.

641
00:30:17,083 --> 00:30:18,600
We'll make progress together.

642
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:20,040
That's right.

643
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:22,720
Shi, Qing Ye is the top student in our class.

644
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:25,559
And besides, there's also me.
I'll be there to help.

645
00:30:25,559 --> 00:30:27,160
Good grades

646
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:29,119
take time.

647
00:30:29,119 --> 00:30:30,640
Let's take it slow. Don't rush.

648
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:33,440
Uncle, Changdao and Zhazhating are both great.

649
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:35,279
But if we stay here our whole lives,

650
00:30:35,279 --> 00:30:37,559
we'll just be repeating our parents' lives.

651
00:30:37,559 --> 00:30:38,680
But if

652
00:30:38,680 --> 00:30:40,394
you allow Shi Min to have a try,

653
00:30:40,394 --> 00:30:43,607
it'll at least open up one more door for her.

654
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:51,602
Fine, I agree.

655
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:54,599
- Your dad agreed.
- Come on.

656
00:30:54,599 --> 00:30:57,440
- He agreed.
- Let's all raise our glasses to celebrate.

657
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:59,720
- You really mean it?
- Yes, I mean it. Don't cry.

658
00:30:59,720 --> 00:31:01,079
Let's welcome Shi Min back to school.

659
00:31:01,079 --> 00:31:02,839
- Come on.
- Come on, cheers.

660
00:31:02,839 --> 00:31:05,839
Cheers, cheers.

661
00:31:05,839 --> 00:31:07,200
- Welcome!
- Cheers.

662
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:08,799
Cheers.

663
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:12,696
Come on, sit down.

664
00:31:28,119 --> 00:31:29,440
I never knew

665
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:31,920
Hu had such a niche talent.

666
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:33,519
Actually, Hu wanted to learn piano

667
00:31:33,519 --> 00:31:35,519
when he was little.

668
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:39,279
Piano and harmonica.

669
00:31:39,279 --> 00:31:41,720
They are worlds apart.

670
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:43,240
His mom said

671
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:44,293
piano and harmonica

672
00:31:44,293 --> 00:31:46,412
are both instruments anyway.

673
00:31:47,359 --> 00:31:48,880
In Zhazhating,

674
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:51,279
you can't make a living with this.

675
00:31:58,079 --> 00:32:00,839
But now I don't think that way.

676
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:05,319
Ever since this summer,

677
00:32:05,319 --> 00:32:07,920
so many things feel different.

678
00:32:25,559 --> 00:32:27,240
Perhaps

679
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:28,967
to Shi Min,

680
00:32:28,967 --> 00:32:30,759
there's no difference

681
00:32:30,759 --> 00:32:33,400
whether Hu plays

682
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:35,171
piano or harmonica.

683
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:40,280
It's really lucky to have someone

684
00:32:40,280 --> 00:32:42,202
who truly gets you.

685
00:32:45,759 --> 00:32:47,120
For me,

686
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:49,047
you're that someone.

687
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,088
It feels so good.

688
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:17,107
It feels so good.

689
00:33:58,519 --> 00:34:00,680
- Not bad.
- Yeah, nice.

690
00:34:07,519 --> 00:34:09,960
Get over here and dance. Come on.

691
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:12,400
Come on, let's dance together.

692
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:15,039
Just relax. Come on, come on.

693
00:34:15,039 --> 00:34:17,599
Come on, Mr. Zhu. Join us.

694
00:34:17,599 --> 00:34:19,639
- Come on.
- Come on, come on.

695
00:34:19,639 --> 00:34:21,639
Let's do it together.

696
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:26,360
Come on. Here we go.

697
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:28,567
Follow me.

698
00:34:44,159 --> 00:34:45,400
<i>There's no going</i>

699
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:48,520
<i>back in life.</i>

700
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:51,320
<i>On this one-way journey,</i>

701
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:53,239
<i>all we can do</i>

702
00:34:53,239 --> 00:34:55,360
<i>is think carefully and decide wisely</i>

703
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:58,000
<i>at every choice,</i>

704
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,280
<i>and try to leave no regrets behind.</i>

705
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:02,599
<i>But if regrets find you, don't lose heart.</i>

706
00:35:02,599 --> 00:35:04,000
<i>Face them calmly and see</i>

707
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:07,040
<i>if there's a chance to make things right.</i>

708
00:35:07,040 --> 00:35:09,440
<i>If everything is already beyond change,</i>

709
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:11,039
<i>embrace it with courage.</i>

710
00:35:11,039 --> 00:35:12,480
<i>Let go of your regrets,</i>

711
00:35:12,480 --> 00:35:14,600
<i>and keep sailing</i>

712
00:35:14,600 --> 00:35:17,103
<i>toward a beautiful future.</i>

713
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:37,920
Let's stop here.

714
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:39,639
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

715
00:35:39,639 --> 00:35:41,199
Thank you, my friend.

716
00:35:41,199 --> 00:35:42,760
I should be thanking you all.

717
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:43,920
Here's a small gift for you.

718
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:46,159
Some fresh seafood.
The only thing we never run out of.

719
00:35:46,159 --> 00:35:48,045
- You're too kind.
- Thanks for the gift.

720
00:35:48,045 --> 00:35:50,240
Actually, you should stay for a few more days.

721
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:52,520
I've got my mom at home
who needs looking after.

722
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:54,400
If not, we'd love to stay.

723
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:56,360
Just let the kids stay here a bit longer.

724
00:35:56,360 --> 00:35:57,519
They can lend you a hand.

725
00:35:57,519 --> 00:35:59,599
And they can relax here.

726
00:35:59,599 --> 00:36:00,920
It's a deal then.

727
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:04,080
Next time, bring the whole family along.
I'll cover your stay and meals.

728
00:36:04,080 --> 00:36:06,079
- No problem. Thank you.
- That's great.

729
00:36:06,079 --> 00:36:08,639
Mr. Zhu, and all you aunties.

730
00:36:08,639 --> 00:36:10,400
Sorry for the trouble.

731
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:14,599
This is what we should do. It's okay.

732
00:36:14,599 --> 00:36:17,320
Shi, Min Min really is sweet.

733
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:18,679
- Yes, she is.
- Definitely.

734
00:36:18,679 --> 00:36:20,024
Hu,

735
00:36:20,024 --> 00:36:21,160
do what you can to help.

736
00:36:21,160 --> 00:36:22,199
Got it, Mom.

737
00:36:22,199 --> 00:36:23,480
Wu,

738
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:25,105
Ye is...

739
00:36:25,105 --> 00:36:26,840
Don't worry. I'll look after her.

740
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:28,386
Good boy.

741
00:36:29,440 --> 00:36:31,519
Everyone, time to go.

742
00:36:31,519 --> 00:36:33,639
- I still have to drive you all back.
- Coming, son.

743
00:36:33,639 --> 00:36:34,920
It's okay. We'll be back the day after.

744
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:36,320
- Don't worry, Auntie.
- Take care of yourselves.

745
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:38,239
- Hurry, get in the car. Come on.
- Bye.

746
00:36:38,239 --> 00:36:40,000
- Drive slowly.
- Be safe on the road.

747
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,119
- Bye, Mom.
- Bye.

748
00:36:41,119 --> 00:36:42,833
Drive safe.

749
00:36:49,653 --> 00:36:51,506
- Let's head back.
- Okay.

750
00:37:14,079 --> 00:37:15,783
What are you thinking about?

751
00:37:17,235 --> 00:37:19,202
My dad.

752
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:24,885
Want to talk about it?

753
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:28,800
But if it's not a good time, forget it.

754
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,880
I can tell you.

755
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:35,600
My dad

756
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:37,360
didn't really

757
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:38,840
care about

758
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:40,840
me much.

759
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:43,440
But when it was a big moment,

760
00:37:43,440 --> 00:37:45,639
he loved to take control.

761
00:37:45,639 --> 00:37:47,400
Every time he went on a business trip,

762
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:49,525
he brought back gifts for my mom and me.

763
00:37:49,525 --> 00:37:51,560
But actually, he didn't buy them himself.

764
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:52,920
He always had his secretaries do it.

765
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:54,719
I never liked those things.

766
00:37:54,719 --> 00:37:56,159
Have you ever heard of

767
00:37:56,159 --> 00:37:58,000
a dad giving his daughter

768
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:00,361
red‑bottomed high heels?

769
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:03,080
Maybe

770
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:06,262
he thought you were
at the age to own a pair of heels.

771
00:38:06,880 --> 00:38:09,120
Not at all.

772
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:11,080
It's because he was carrying on

773
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:12,640
with those secretaries.

774
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:14,159
Those women

775
00:38:14,159 --> 00:38:16,040
bought me heels

776
00:38:16,040 --> 00:38:18,152
just to spite my mom.

777
00:38:19,039 --> 00:38:20,720
After my mom passed away,

778
00:38:20,720 --> 00:38:23,400
they all rushed to take her place.

779
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:24,840
But then,

780
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:26,400
my dad got into trouble.

781
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:28,519
They ran away faster than anyone.

782
00:38:28,519 --> 00:38:31,039
Ironic, isn't it?

783
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,680
Any news

784
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:38,400
about your dad?

785
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:41,159
No.

786
00:38:41,159 --> 00:38:42,560
Look at the bright side.

787
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:44,915
No news is good news.

788
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:53,545
You cold?

789
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:56,440
Now I get it.

790
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:57,920
Biting cold

791
00:38:57,920 --> 00:38:58,992
isn't just a saying.

792
00:38:58,992 --> 00:39:00,893
It's real.

793
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:10,433
Put this on.

794
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:35,282
Let's go.

795
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:07,641
Let's go.

796
00:40:11,520 --> 00:40:13,308
Off we go.

797
00:40:23,025 --> 00:40:24,120
Where are you going?

798
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:25,600
T-To have some fun.

799
00:40:25,600 --> 00:40:27,719
Why didn't you wait for me?

800
00:40:27,719 --> 00:40:29,280
Didn't expect you to be this fast.

801
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:30,819
There's a lot you don't know.

802
00:40:30,819 --> 00:40:32,761
Go ask around.

803
00:40:35,239 --> 00:40:36,920
- Come on, let's go.
- Let's hit the road.

804
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:38,081
Go, go, go.

805
00:40:38,081 --> 00:40:40,776
- Here we go.
- Let's go.

806
00:40:41,639 --> 00:40:44,695
- One, two. One, two.
- Halt.

807
00:40:44,695 --> 00:40:45,840
Turn right.

808
00:40:45,840 --> 00:40:47,639
- Right face.
- Right face.

809
00:40:47,639 --> 00:40:49,840
To the sea!

810
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:52,679
To freedom!

811
00:40:55,639 --> 00:40:58,440
- Go!
- Let's go!

812
00:42:17,680 --> 00:42:20,915
Cheers!

813
00:42:23,280 --> 00:42:25,000
Tastes good. So many seeds.

814
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:26,519
Working on the island is tiring.

815
00:42:26,519 --> 00:42:29,159
But this is so much fun.
I almost want to live here.

816
00:42:29,159 --> 00:42:30,680
You only tried it out.

817
00:42:30,680 --> 00:42:31,752
It's just the novelty.

818
00:42:31,752 --> 00:42:35,920
A few months here and you'll think differently.

819
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:38,320
Setting aside practical matters,

820
00:42:38,320 --> 00:42:40,236
what do you guys want to do someday?

821
00:42:40,800 --> 00:42:42,400
I...

822
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:44,159
I want to be a singer.

823
00:42:44,159 --> 00:42:46,199
- A singer?
- Can't I even dream?

824
00:42:46,199 --> 00:42:47,903
Of course you can. That sounds great.

825
00:42:47,903 --> 00:42:49,519
You rapped before.

826
00:42:49,519 --> 00:42:52,719
You're good. I believe in you.

827
00:42:52,719 --> 00:42:53,760
I…

828
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:55,592
I want to be a painter.

829
00:42:55,592 --> 00:42:58,000
But it's just a dream.

830
00:42:59,360 --> 00:43:00,480
Me?

831
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:02,199
I want to...

832
00:43:02,199 --> 00:43:03,520
Be a truck driver.

833
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:05,473
You still remember that?

834
00:43:05,473 --> 00:43:07,360
Man, you're such a good friend.

835
00:43:07,360 --> 00:43:09,679
You've been saying that since first grade.

836
00:43:09,679 --> 00:43:12,079
My ears are about to fall off.

837
00:43:12,079 --> 00:43:13,840
Wait, your family runs boats.

838
00:43:13,840 --> 00:43:15,079
How come you want to drive a truck?

839
00:43:15,079 --> 00:43:16,880
I've been on boats since I was a kid.

840
00:43:16,880 --> 00:43:19,360
All I see is endless water.

841
00:43:19,360 --> 00:43:21,480
I want to drive a truck because every trip

842
00:43:21,480 --> 00:43:25,366
takes you somewhere new with different views.

843
00:43:25,366 --> 00:43:27,800
But your parents want you to take over

844
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:29,320
the boat business and the mahjong parlor,

845
00:43:29,320 --> 00:43:30,840
or at least one of them.

846
00:43:30,840 --> 00:43:33,320
That's just the backup they gave me.

847
00:43:33,320 --> 00:43:34,560
Actually,

848
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:36,800
all fishermen want their children
to return to the land.

849
00:43:36,800 --> 00:43:38,040
Like my dad.

850
00:43:38,040 --> 00:43:39,159
He's a shark.

851
00:43:39,159 --> 00:43:40,760
He loves splashing around in the sea.

852
00:43:40,760 --> 00:43:42,000
But I'm a dog.

853
00:43:42,000 --> 00:43:45,079
I need to run wild on land.

